{"parentUuid":"c2f49395-4250-4588-8643-3abb59747d4b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ac7c99e6fe1d41e66","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018FmWNuEhKWdWhXuUVxPczE","type":"tool_result","content":"# Darwin Gödel Machine: Key Findings\n\n## Foundation Model Status\n\nThe webpage does not contain explicit quotes stating that foundation models are frozen or that only the agent scaffolding is modified. The document mentions DGM \"leverages foundation models to propose code improvements\" and discusses modifying \"its own Python codebase,\" but does not directly state whether the base models themselves remain unmodified.\n\nHowever, one forward-looking statement suggests future work may involve the base models:\n\n> \"Future work will involve scaling up the approach and even letting it improve the training of the foundation models at its core.\"\n\nThis implies the current implementation does not modify foundation model training.\n\n## Performance Improvements\n\n**SWE-bench:**\n> \"On SWE-bench, the DGM automatically improved its performance from 20.0% to 50.0%.\"\n\n**Polyglot:**\n> \"On Polyglot, the DGM jumped performance from an initial 14.2% to 30.7%, which far surpasses the representative hand-designed agent by Aider.\""}]},"uuid":"c4592f76-0d46-49f2-8c6b-fbdeb4ffe4b2","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:11.867Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":21225,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Darwin Gödel Machine: Key Findings\n\n## Foundation Model Status\n\nThe webpage does not contain explicit quotes stating that foundation models are frozen or that only the agent scaffolding is modified. The document mentions DGM \"leverages foundation models to propose code improvements\" and discusses modifying \"its own Python codebase,\" but does not directly state whether the base models themselves remain unmodified.\n\nHowever, one forward-looking statement suggests future work may involve the base models:\n\n> \"Future work will involve scaling up the approach and even letting it improve the training of the foundation models at its core.\"\n\nThis implies the current implementation does not modify foundation model training.\n\n## Performance Improvements\n\n**SWE-bench:**\n> \"On SWE-bench, the DGM automatically improved its performance from 20.0% to 50.0%.\"\n\n**Polyglot:**\n> \"On Polyglot, the DGM jumped performance from an initial 14.2% to 30.7%, which far surpasses the representative hand-designed agent by Aider.\"","durationMs":4464,"url":"https://sakana.ai/dgm/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c2f49395-4250-4588-8643-3abb59747d4b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"0d3d2300-0bae-44d5-9439-8172a7b949eb","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ac7c99e6fe1d41e66","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TgEBXtUy5HkYs2gzt2tysf","type":"tool_result","content":"# Darwin Gödel Machine: Key Quotes and Performance Metrics\n\n**On Self-Modification:**\n\"iteratively modifies its own code (thereby also improving its ability to modify its own codebase)\"\n\n**On Validation Approach:**\n\"empirically validates each change using coding benchmarks\"\n\n**On Architecture:**\n\"maintains an archive of generated coding agents. It grows the archive by sampling an agent from it and using a foundation model to create a new, interesting, version\"\n\n**Performance Gains:**\n- SWE-bench: improved \"from 20.0% to 50.0%\"\n- Polyglot: increased \"from 14.2% to 30.7%\"\n\n**Key Capability:**\nThe system \"automatically improves its coding capabilities (e.g., better code editing tools, long-context window management, peer-review mechanisms)\"\n\nThe research indicates the DGM uses foundation models to generate agent variations while the agents themselves—not the foundation models—are modified and archived across iterations."}]},"uuid":"6a2a5ee0-8c23-443e-92c4-6ec90c8dfc44","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:14.292Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":48792,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Darwin Gödel Machine: Key Quotes and Performance Metrics\n\n**On Self-Modification:**\n\"iteratively modifies its own code (thereby also improving its ability to modify its own codebase)\"\n\n**On Validation Approach:**\n\"empirically validates each change using coding benchmarks\"\n\n**On Architecture:**\n\"maintains an archive of generated coding agents. It grows the archive by sampling an agent from it and using a foundation model to create a new, interesting, version\"\n\n**Performance Gains:**\n- SWE-bench: improved \"from 20.0% to 50.0%\"\n- Polyglot: increased \"from 14.2% to 30.7%\"\n\n**Key Capability:**\nThe system \"automatically improves its coding capabilities (e.g., better code editing tools, long-context window management, peer-review mechanisms)\"\n\nThe research indicates the DGM uses foundation models to generate agent variations while the agents themselves—not the foundation models—are modified and archived across iterations.","durationMs":5104,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0d3d2300-0bae-44d5-9439-8172a7b949eb","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"a35cee8f-1b55-410c-9511-622632781bb7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ac7c99e6fe1d41e66","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JAopeLzbkLYFtaEPy3fKtw","type":"tool_result","content":"# Key Findings on RLVR vs Base Models\n\n**RLVR-trained models vs base model at large k:**\n\"the base models achieve a higher pass@k score when k is large\"\n\n**Reasoning paths already embedded in base model:**\n\"the observed reasoning abilities originate from and are bounded by the base model\"\n\n**Capability bounded by base model:**\n\"Treating the base model as an upper bound, our quantitative analysis shows that six popular RLVR algorithms perform similarly and remain far from optimal\"\n\n**RLVR improves sampling efficiency rather than adding new capabilities:**\nThe abstract states current RLVR \"does not elicit fundamentally new reasoning patterns\" despite outperforming base models at small k values.\n\n**Distillation expanding capabilities:**\n\"we find that distillation can introduce new reasoning patterns from the teacher and genuinely expand the model's reasoning capabilities\""}]},"uuid":"fe4cd45e-8f43-4a4a-9864-454adecd19c0","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:14.501Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":48797,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Key Findings on RLVR vs Base Models\n\n**RLVR-trained models vs base model at large k:**\n\"the base models achieve a higher pass@k score when k is large\"\n\n**Reasoning paths already embedded in base model:**\n\"the observed reasoning abilities originate from and are bounded by the base model\"\n\n**Capability bounded by base model:**\n\"Treating the base model as an upper bound, our quantitative analysis shows that six popular RLVR algorithms perform similarly and remain far from optimal\"\n\n**RLVR improves sampling efficiency rather than adding new capabilities:**\nThe abstract states current RLVR \"does not elicit fundamentally new reasoning patterns\" despite outperforming base models at small k values.\n\n**Distillation expanding capabilities:**\n\"we find that distillation can introduce new reasoning patterns from the teacher and genuinely expand the model's reasoning capabilities\"","durationMs":3449,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.13837"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a35cee8f-1b55-410c-9511-622632781bb7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
