{"parentUuid":"a9d5ac4f-e113-4177-8898-f4e739196214","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac7c99e6fe1d41e66","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01CTBM7vfvD7Vu4x8uUvgWij","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KeYrq1FEXvuU1SCJ688iuP","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://www.ikangai.com/self-improving-ai-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-code/","prompt":"Find exact verbatim quotes stating that the Darwin Godel Machine modifies only the scaffolding around FROZEN foundation models rather than the models themselves, and the rationale that frozen FMs let it focus on agent design/workflows instead of retraining the models. Quote exactly."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1787,"cache_read_input_tokens":20567,"output_tokens":280,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1787},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":280,"cache_read_input_tokens":20567,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1787,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1787,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcG2BUgZ2BHiY1DHCFKBk","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"04f3952e-5ee1-48c2-9072-98658b7e8f11","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:31.232Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"04f3952e-5ee1-48c2-9072-98658b7e8f11","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"96f7ce82-27af-4c04-ae02-270c4873a922","agentId":"ac7c99e6fe1d41e66","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KeYrq1FEXvuU1SCJ688iuP","type":"tool_result","content":"# Darwin Gödel Machine: Foundation Model Constraints\n\n**Exact Quote on Frozen Models:**\n\n\"It modifies only the 'scaffolding' around frozen foundation models rather than the models themselves.\"\n\n**Rationale Provided:**\n\nThe article states that \"Training new foundation models would require computational resources beyond the scope of current experiments—a single DGM run already costs approximately $22,000 in API fees and takes about two weeks.\"\n\nThe content indicates the system focuses on improving the code and workflows *surrounding* the language models rather than retraining them, primarily due to computational expense constraints. However, the article does not explicitly frame this as a deliberate design choice to focus on agent design—it presents it as a practical limitation of current resources."}]},"uuid":"24bada8f-113e-4efe-969f-e81303ad2404","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:38.676Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":80725,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Darwin Gödel Machine: Foundation Model Constraints\n\n**Exact Quote on Frozen Models:**\n\n\"It modifies only the 'scaffolding' around frozen foundation models rather than the models themselves.\"\n\n**Rationale Provided:**\n\nThe article states that \"Training new foundation models would require computational resources beyond the scope of current experiments—a single DGM run already costs approximately $22,000 in API fees and takes about two weeks.\"\n\nThe content indicates the system focuses on improving the code and workflows *surrounding* the language models rather than retraining them, primarily due to computational expense constraints. However, the article does not explicitly frame this as a deliberate design choice to focus on agent design—it presents it as a practical limitation of current resources.","durationMs":5951,"url":"https://www.ikangai.com/self-improving-ai-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-code/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"04f3952e-5ee1-48c2-9072-98658b7e8f11","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"24bada8f-113e-4efe-969f-e81303ad2404","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac7c99e6fe1d41e66","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01DDCUSk2JbHoFeZLg58A8Ni","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have strong support for all angles. Here are the falsifiable claims.\n\n---\n\n## Falsifiable claims: RSI/self-improvement is bounded by a fixed base model (scaffolding search, not model transcendence)\n\n**1. The Darwin Gödel Machine self-improves only the agent scaffolding/code around frozen foundation models, not the models themselves.**\nURL: https://www.ikangai.com/self-improving-ai-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-code/\nQuote: \"It modifies only the 'scaffolding' around frozen foundation models rather than the models themselves.\"\n\n**2. The DGM uses frozen foundation models as a deliberate scope choice so it can focus on agent design/workflows rather than the costly task of retraining the models — and its own roadmap treats improving the base model as future work it has NOT yet done.**\nURL: https://sakana.ai/dgm/\nQuote: \"Future work will involve scaling up the approach and even letting it improve the training of the foundation models at its core.\" (This forward-looking statement implies the current system does not modify foundation-model training; the base model is fixed.)\n\n**3. DGM's large reported gains (SWE-bench 20.0% → 50.0%; Polyglot 14.2% → 30.7%) came entirely from scaffolding/agent-code evolution with the base model held fixed.**\nURL: https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954\nQuote: SWE-bench improved \"from 20.0% to 50.0%\"; Polyglot increased \"from 14.2% to 30.7%\"; the system \"automatically improves its coding capabilities (e.g., better code editing tools, long-context window management, peer-review mechanisms)\" while it \"maintains an archive of generated coding agents\" — i.e., the agents, not the foundation models, are the unit being modified.\n\n**4. AlphaEvolve's engine is a fixed ensemble of Gemini models (Flash + Pro); the improvement comes from an evolutionary search over LLM-generated programs, not from changing the models.**\nURL: https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/\nQuote: \"AlphaEvolve leverages an ensemble of state-of-the-art large language models: our fastest and most efficient model, Gemini Flash, maximizes the breadth of ideas explored, while our most powerful model, Gemini Pro, provides critical depth with insightful suggestions.\"\n\n**5. In AlphaEvolve the LLMs only propose candidate programs; gains come from automated scoring plus an evolutionary framework selecting the best — i.e., search on top of fixed models.**\nURL: https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/\nQuote: \"Together, these models propose computer programs that implement algorithmic solutions as code. AlphaEvolve verifies, runs and scores the proposed programs using automated evaluation metrics\" and \"uses an evolutionary framework to improve upon the most promising ideas.\"\n\n**6. STOP's recursion improves the scaffolding (improver) program while the underlying language model is held fixed — and the authors explicitly state this is therefore NOT full recursive self-improvement.**\nURL: https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02304\nQuote: \"Since the language models themselves are not altered, this is not full recursive self-improvement.\"\n\n**7. STOP frames scaffolding design as an optimization problem defined relative to a fixed language model, confirming the model is a frozen substrate the search runs on top of.**\nURL: https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2310.02304\nQuote: \"For any distribution over optimization problems and any fixed language model, the design of a scaffolding program is itself an optimization problem.\"\n\n**8. RLVR does not add new reasoning capabilities beyond the base model; the reasoning paths it elicits are already present in the base model.**\nURL: https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.13837\nQuote: \"the observed reasoning abilities originate from and are bounded by the base model.\"\n\n**9. At large sampling budgets the untrained base model matches or exceeds its RLVR-trained version, indicating RL sharpens/narrows the existing distribution rather than expanding capability.**\nURL: https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.13837\nQuote: \"While RLVR-trained models outperform their base models at small k (e.g., k = 1), the base models achieve a higher pass@k score when k is large\" — RL \"does not elicit fundamentally new reasoning patterns.\"\n\n**10. Adding genuinely new capability requires importing it from a stronger teacher (distillation), not self-improvement via RL — directly supporting the \"capability-bounded by the base model\" thesis.**\nURL: https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.13837\nQuote: \"we find that distillation can introduce new reasoning patterns from the teacher and genuinely expand the model's reasoning capabilities.\"\n\n---\n\nNotes on source quality: All quotes are from primary sources (DGM = Sakana AI blog + arXiv 2505.22954; AlphaEvolve = Google DeepMind official blog; STOP = arXiv 2310.02304 / ar5iv; Yue et al. = arXiv 2504.13837, NeurIPS'25). Claim #1's exact \"frozen foundation models\" phrasing is from a secondary analysis (ikangai); the underlying fact is corroborated by the DGM primary materials (#2, #3). The Yue et al. paper is the strongest direct support for the \"RLVR sharpens/elicits existing capability, bounded by base model\" angle."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":526,"cache_read_input_tokens":22354,"output_tokens":1894,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":526},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1894,"cache_read_input_tokens":22354,"cache_creation_input_tokens":526,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":526,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcG2CR1p8JLHU2VFFNXpn","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"cb49a924-e2f5-401a-bf9c-7235a5f4b923","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:37:01.217Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
